post_text: Great article on SHS alum, Kayla Sampson
shared_text:
34th Expeditionary Combat Aviation Brigade
September 3 at 4:28 AM ·

At the age of 21 years old, Sgt. Kayla Sampson is the youngest flight medic assigned with the Indiana National Guard MEDEVAC unit currently deployed to the Middle East in support of Operation Inherent Resolve and Operation Spartan Shield. She is also the newest flight medic, having just boarded for the position in July of 2019.

“They called me October 1st and said “we need another medic to deploy are you willing? We leave in 20 days,”" said Sampson. “I was pretty excited because I was wanting the experience, I wanted to deploy, and wanted to go, I wanted to do and see."

Sampson's dedication to service embodies the National Guard's mission to remain #AlwaysReady

To read the full story: https://www.dvidshub.net/news/377377/sgt-kayla-sampson-flight-medic

C Company 2-238th GSAB - Hoosier Dustoff | #RedDevils | #IndianaNationalGuard

At this time, Scott 2 is working closely with the Scott County Health Department on contact tracing to identify any close contacts of this particular student. We thank you again for your continued patience, support, and understanding as we navigate these very challenging times.

Respectfully,
Marc Slaton, Ed.D.

At this time, Scott 2 is working closely with the Scott County Health Department on contact tracing to identify any close contacts of this particular student.

Please know that per protocol, all close contacts will be notified. Thus, you will receive communication from the Scott County Health Department or Scott County School District 2 if your student is identified as a close contact. If your student is determined to be a close contact, you will receive further guidance when you are contacted.

The Scott 2 staff is following the protocols established in the Scott 2 Reopening Plan which includes cleaning and disinfecting school buildings and bus transportation every day.

Respectfully,
Marc Slaton, Ed.D.

With 4 Pixellot cameras live streaming over 100 home events, advertisers have a unique opportunity to partner with Scottsburg High School and its student athletes. With attendance being limited due to COVID-19 restrictions, your advertising reach will be greater than ever as followers may opt to watch live from any device anywhere in the world. Each live streamed event will have 3 screen locations you can advertise. Charles E. Meyer Gymnasium (Warriorette & Warrior Basketball)
McClain Hall (Girls & Boys Volleyball, Wrestling)
David Spann Field (Girls & Boys Soccer)

post_text: Congrats Hannah!
shared_text:
Whats The Buzz Around The Burg
June 24 at 4:58 PM ·

A great big CONGRATULATIONS to Hannah Sipe from Scott County, she recently punched her ticket to Loretta Lynn’s AMA Amateur National Motocross Championship this past weekend at Lincoln Trail Motocross by getting fifth place overall.
Loretta Lynn’s will run from August 3rd through August 8th where Hannah will race against the top 42 fastest girls in the nation. Nearly 22,000 racers attempt to qualify in 35 classes for the 1,446 positions available at nationals and Hannah has officially filled one of those spots in the Girls 11-16 class!
Hannah will be a Freshman this fall at Scottsburg Senior High School. Crongratluations Hannah! We are proud of you!

City of Scottsburg

JOIN US TODAY 🎉🎓
Celebrate our graduating Seniors from Scottsburg High School.
PARADE STARTS AT 2PM - BEGINS AT HIGH SCHOOL- around Downtown Square and back to High School!

Message from the Mayor -
Scottsburg High School graduates of 2020 walked the the halls as a senior for the last time yesterday. They are now alumni. Due to the covid 19 pandemic, their walk down the aisle was limited to an attendance of 8.
Today June the 7th, there will be a parade for the seniors at 2pm (they will be in their cars, trucks or floats).The parade will begin at the high school, going north to the intersection with highway 56, then turning east to the downtown square. They will then go around the square and return back to the high school for one final lap.
The city will be filming, PLEASE COME OUT TODAY AND SUPPORT OUR GRADUATES.
THANK YOU,
Mayor Terry Amick

post_text: We here at SCSD2 finished up our feeding program for the regular school year today. I just wanted to say thank you so much to a few groups and individuals. First of all thank you lunch ladies, bus drivers, and custodians, it was hard work for everyone, cooking in hot kitchens, lifting heavy boxes and coolers. Standing outside in the rain and cold. But when you see our students running up to get their lunches with a smile on their face it is all well worth it￼￼. Special thanks to Sue Hart for coming up with delicious meals every day and breakfast. Thank-you Dr. Casey Brewster for pinpointing where to place the buses for the most coverage. Dr. Brewster is truly a genius with data and information. And lastly Dr. Marc Slaton and our School Board for permitting us to move forward with this program. Our students had full bellies during this craziness because of all of you￼.

We will release the date that the Graduation Video will play for the general public at a later date. It will likely be somewhere around mid to late June. In order to meet the CDC, state, and local health department guidelines, the SHS Campus will be closed on June 5 and 6 to only the graduates and up to 8 family members at their assigned times and those staff who are working the "individual ceremonies".

We will release more information on the June 7th City of Scottsburg Class of 2020 Parade as soon as we iron out some of the final details. Absolutely amazing school leader but even better person. Scott 2 has been blessed by Ms. Nass over these past 25 years and Kristin has been a huge asset to our leadership team. She has truly helped our administrative team to grow and develop into the leaders we are today. I said back in December that you never fill those shoes, you just go get another pair to put on and I truly mean that.

I hate that it is coming to close for her in the midst of this pandemic because I know how much every single one of her students, their families, and her staff mean to her and I know how so badly she misses those daily face to face interactions!

Kristin- thanks for your leadership, your passion, your dedication, your energy, and your commitment to Scott 2 and to SMS!

post_text:
MAY 6TH IS SCHOOL NURSE'S DAY

It's time to celebrate!!!!!

Scott County School District 2 is blessed to have experienced and professional nurses at all 6 school buildings.

Scott 2 school nurses not only provide first aid for students who are injured or ill but also provide a wide range of specialized care to all students and staff in their buildings. They work with the parent, staff, and physicians to provide the student with the best possible care in the school environment.

Remember:
Students must be Healthy to be Educated and Educated to be Healthy

**UPDATE***

Per Stephen Carey Director of Emergency Preparedness at SMH -

The masks are for those patients that come in and test NEGATIVE, but they are in a hospital setting and want some protection. He stated they do not have a shortage, but the demand is high.
Also they are doing a lot of cleaning, and they are going through a lot of bleach so they do need Disinfecting Bleach, Disinfecting Bleach Wipes,(Must be the Disinfecting kind) and Homemade Masks.

If anyone has anything to donate please call Stephen at 812-820-7640 or Erica Thompson at 812-752-8500

shared_text:
Scottsburg Warrior Football
April 13 at 10:13 PM ·

Our thoughts and prayers go out to the Loggan Family and the North Central Panther Family. Paul Loggan unfortunately lost his battle with COVID-19. Paul was a great advocate for high school football and athletics in Indiana. I was at a conference rival school (Ben Davis) to Paul, yet he always went out of his way to say hi and ask how I was doing at the IFCA meetings and Other events. He was a great man who could light up a stadium with his smile. May his legacy live on through IHSAA Athletics! Tonight we salute Coach Loggan by lighting up Warrior Field!#paulstrong
-Coach Mullins

post_text:
Congrats to our very own Dr. Shannon Mount!

Amid the COVID-19 crisis and using distance technology, Shannon Mount successfully defended her dissertation to her full University of Louisville dissertation committee. "We are all learning to adjust to this new situation. I had originally scheduled my dissertation defense during SCSD2's spring break. Then as the COVID-19 crisis closed in, I was afraid it wouldn't happen. Thankfully, UofL was responding rapidly and put mechanisms in place to allow me to accomplish my oral defense from Scott Co."

Mount's dissertation was entitled Coparenting and School Success: Perspectives of Fathers. We want to congratulate Dr. Mount on her accomplishment.

post_text: Congrats Lexie!
shared_text:
The Scott County Herald - The Clark County Herald Newspapers
March 4 at 1:34 PM ·

Lexie Amhrein earns highest academic honor for Big 12 conference at Baylor University

Lexie Amrhein, a Scottsburg 2016 graduate, was recently awarded the Dr. Gerald Lage Academic Acheivement Award at Baylor University in Waco, Texas. The award is the most prestigious recognition for student athletes in the Big 12 conference.
Lexie is currently a senior at Baylor University and is an environmental science major. She is also a member of the Acrobatics and Tumbling Team, which are seeking their 6th straight national championship. Lexie's overall grade point average is 3.92. Her hard work has helped her earn an internship in South Africa in May of 2020. She will be diving and researching the earthly benefits of kelp forests for our environment. Photo credit to Baylor University.

Awesome opportunity today for our SHS Advanced Manufacturing Students! We toured the Seymour Cummins Engine Plant and learned all about their manufacturing and testing processes. It made me very proud to run into a Scottsburg High School Alum and former student, Daniel Miskell, who is now employed there. It was a great experience! Thanks to Mid-America Science Park for helping make this possible for our students.

post_text: Very proud of our SMS Spellers!
shared_text:
The Scott County Herald - The Clark County Herald Newspapers
November 15, 2019 at 1:21 PM ·

Scottsburg Middle School Spell Bowl team goes to state finals

For the first time ever, the Scottsburg Middle School Spell Bowl team is going to state competition! Area Junior Academic Spell Bowl competitions were held throughout the state on Tuesday, November 5th. The SMS team competed in Sellersburg, and after eight rounds featuring a possible 1625 words, they won first place in their division. Student spellers Skylar Herald and Emma Spaulding earned a near-perfect score, correctly spelling eight of nine words. Overall, only four schools in Indiana qualify for state competition in Class 2, which makes their accomplishment even more impressive.

They were amazing!!!!! Awards at 1:45. It’s gonna be tough to advance... but regardless of placement, we are so proud of you!!!!!!! It’s been difficult to manage all the fun things we’ve done this year and still pull off a solid, clean performance at prelims! THEY DID IT!!! Now we wait....
